# GMX Fork Testing Environment Variables

# ============================================================================
# Required Configuration
# ============================================================================

# Arbitrum RPC URL (required for both Foundry and Anvil)
# You can use a public RPC or a provider like Alchemy/Infura for better performance
#
# Free options:
#   - https://arb1.arbitrum.io/rpc (public RPC, may be rate-limited)
#
# Paid/API key options (recommended for better reliability):
#   - https://arb-mainnet.g.alchemy.com/v2/YOUR_API_KEY
#   - https://arbitrum-mainnet.infura.io/v3/YOUR_API_KEY
ARBITRUM_RPC_URL=https://arb1.arbitrum.io/rpc

# ============================================================================
# Usage Notes
# ============================================================================
#
# FOUNDRY USERS:
#   Run tests directly with:
#   forge test --fork-url $ARBITRUM_RPC_URL -vv
#
# ANVIL USERS:
#   1. Start Anvil fork in one terminal:
#      npm run anvil:start
#
#   2. Run TypeScript tests in another terminal:
#      npm run test:open    # Test opening a position
#      npm run test:close   # Test closing a position
#      npm run test:all     # Run all tests
#
# ============================================================================
